CNCP v1 23179
{
  "concept": "vuejs/core#10203: error TS2322 on generic ref<Map<K>> assignment",
  "version": "1.0",
  "created_at": "2026-03-15T04:23:12.147571+00:00",
  "text": "error TS2322 on generic ref<Map<K>> assignment\n\n### Vue version\n\n3.3.11\n\n### Link to minimal reproduction\n\nhttps://github.com/goodwan/vue3-generic-ref-map\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\nthe following code compiles in vue 3.3.8 but fails with 3.3.11 and 3.4.15\r\n``` ts\r\n// App.vue\r\nfunction test<K>() {\r\n  const m: Ref<Map<string, K>> = ref(new Map<string, K>())\r\n}\r\n```\r\n\r\nbuild attached github project with vue 3.3.11 to get build error \r\n```\r\nsrc/App.vue:5:9 - error TS2322: Type 'Ref<Map<string, UnwrapRefSimple<K>>>' is not assignable to type 'Ref<Map<string, K>>'.\r\n  Type 'Map<string, UnwrapRefSimple<K>>' is not assignable to type 'Map<string, K>'.\r\n    Type 'UnwrapRefSimple<K>' is not assignable to type 'K'.\r\n      'K' could be instantiated with an arbitrary type which could be unrelated to 'UnwrapRefSimple<K>'.\r\n\r\n5   const m: Ref<Map<string, K>> = ref(new Map<string, K>())\r\n          ~\r\n\r\n```\n\n### What is expected?\n\nassignment should compile\n\n### What is actually happening?\n\nsomething changed in typed declarations for ref and/or Ref that introduced types incompatibility\n\n### System Info\n\n_No response_\n\n### Any additional comments?\n\n_No response_",
  "language": "en",
  "keywords": [
    "scope: types"
  ],
